## Distinguishable in combination (verified via flag pairs)
  -L  # follow links
    | flag adds 5 lines:   File: ".",     ID: c63eb3646de0a34 Namelen: 255     Type: ext2/ext3, Block size: 4096       Fundamental block size: 4096, Blocks: Total: 1937552970 Free: 1606332148 Available: 1508666090, Inodes: Total: 244158464  Free: 239475015
    | flag removes 8 lines:   File: .,   Size: 4096      	Blocks: 8          IO Block: 4096   directory, Device: 254,0	Inode: 149094757   Links: 2, Access: (0755/drwxr-xr-x)  Uid: ( 1000/mmontalbo)   Gid: (  100/   users), Access: 2026-05-14 21:15:03.053952329 -0700
    | stderr changed: stat: cannot read file system information for 'root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash': No such file or directory
    proven via: "-L" "--cached=default" "$(head -n1 input.txt)" "."
  -f  # display file system status instead of file status
    | flag adds 5 lines:   File: ".",     ID: c63eb3646de0a34 Namelen: 255     Type: ext2/ext3, Block size: 4096       Fundamental block size: 4096, Blocks: Total: 1937552970 Free: 1606332148 Available: 1508666090, Inodes: Total: 244158464  Free: 239475015
    | flag removes 8 lines:   File: .,   Size: 4096      	Blocks: 8          IO Block: 4096   directory, Device: 254,0	Inode: 149094757   Links: 2, Access: (0755/drwxr-xr-x)  Uid: ( 1000/mmontalbo)   Gid: (  100/   users), Access: 2026-05-14 21:15:03.053952329 -0700
    | stderr changed: stat: cannot read file system information for 'root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash': No such file or directory
    proven via: "--cached=default" "--file-system" "."
  -t  # print the information in terse form
    | flag adds 1 lines: . 4096 8 41ed 1000 100 fe00 149095177 2 0 0 1778818503 1778818503 1778818503 1778818503 4096
    | flag removes 8 lines:   File: .,   Size: 4096      	Blocks: 8          IO Block: 4096   directory, Device: 254,0	Inode: 149094757   Links: 2, Access: (0755/drwxr-xr-x)  Uid: ( 1000/mmontalbo)   Gid: (  100/   users), Access: 2026-05-14 21:15:03.053952329 -0700
    proven via: "--cached=default" "-t" "$(head -n1 input.txt)" "."

